drm: cix: demote display stack trace logging to debug

The CIX display drivers emit a large amount of normal probe, HPD,
panel, HDCP, and runtime-PM progress logging via dev_info()/pr_info().
Keep real warnings and errors visible, but move the trace-style output
behind dynamic debug so normal boots stay readable.

The DPTX driver can also operate without an external dp_phy reference by
registering its built-in USB-DP/eDP PHY helpers, so report that fallback
at debug level rather than warning on every boot.

---
diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/cix/cix_display.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/cix/cix_display.c
